      "message": "I\u0027m a little concerned about introducing Meson options to override the defaults defined in PDI. My understanding is that, if defaults are defined in PDI, they are part of the interface contract, then allowing each consumer to change them at build time means the documented behavior and the implementation can diverge.\n\n\nIf the defaults are actually intended to be platform-specific, then perhaps they shouldn\u0027t be defined in PDI in the first place and should instead come from a platform configuration layer ? \n\nThe reason that we made them false by default is because , SPDM policies can alter the security model of the system \u0026 redfish model seems to show that an external verifier does the verification of the measurement values (hence an external agent who is responsible for verification also would set the policy as well). https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/85393/comment/04e261c4_832c6f7a/ documents the reasons for the default a bit more elaborately.\n\nCan you comment a bit more on \"why\" we are need this overriding capability in the daemon ?",
